Rating: 4
I love red pepper hummus, and based my dish off Sabra's red pepper hummus. That was the taste I was attempting with this recipe. I used two cans of garbanzo beans, drained, rinsed. I roasted my own peppers over my gas stove burner. I added about a quarter cup of Tahini. And I used about 3 tablespoons of jarred minced garlic. Salt and pepper to taste. Blend about 5 minutes in a food processor. It was perfect!

