Rating: 3
I obviously liked this recipe. I've made it twice this week. I made a few changes. I think 1/3 cup lemon juice is too much. I used at least a Tablespoon less and still had a good lemon kick. Be careful of the size of your garlic cloves. My second attempt was too garlicy - and I adore garlic. The first time, I roasted my red pepper and used it all. The second time I used bottled according to the recipe. I preferred my own for two reasons - the hummus was less red, and the flavor was fresher. Both times I added several pinches of cayenne and cumin and a bit less coriander - to taste. Also about 1/4 tsp salt. BTW - if you have an Indian market nearby, the sesame seeds can be purchased in larger quantities at a fraction of the cost of bottles in your supermarket.

